cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on studying the Internet topology time-series. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the dynamic graph patterns of the Internet topology. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a model to infer the topology in the future. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the parameters in the model and their relationship to graph characteristics. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing and modeling information flow in the Internet topology.
